Class SimpleStoredMap<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.flowpowered.commons.store.SimpleStoredMap<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Named, StoredMap<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    StringToUniqueIntegerMap

    public class SimpleStoredMap<T>
extends Object
implements StoredMap<T>
    Represents a map for mapping Strings to and Object. All conversions are cached in a store.

      • register

        public boolean register(String key,
                        T value)
        Registers a key/id pair with the map. If the id is already in use the method will fail.

        The id must be lower than the min id for the map to prevent clashing with the dynamically allocated ids
        Specified by:
        register in interface StoredMap<T>
        Parameters:
        key - the key to be added
        value - the desired value to be matched to the key
        Returns:

        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the id >= minId
